<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
<title>Verbose Journal - GnoTime</title>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<h1>Verbose Journal for 
<?scm (gtt-show-project-title) ?>
 - 
<?scm (gtt-show-project-desc) ?>
</h1>

This is an example of all of the different task and interval getters 
that can be used to build a report.  There are two tables here:
the first shows only tasks, the second shows tasks and intervals 
intermingled in one table.  Make a copy of this file, and edit it
to create your own custom reports.

<br><br>


<table border=1>
<tr>
<th>Diary Entry</th>
<th>Notes</th>
<th>Billing Status</th>
<th>Billable</th>
<th>Bill Rate</th>
<th>Total Time</th>
<th>Value</th>
<th>Billable Value</th>
</tr>
<?scm

(gtt-show-tasks (gtt-tasks (gtt-linked-project))
    (list   
        ''"<tr>"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-memo       ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-notes      ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-billstatus ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-billable   ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-billrate   ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-time-str   ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-value-str  ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td>"  gtt-task-billable-value-str  ''"</td>\n"
        ''</tr>
    )
)


?>
</table>

<br><br><br>

The table below presents an alternate layout for the journal report.
<br><br><br>

<table border=1>
<tr>
<th>Diary Entry</th>
<th>Start</th>
<th>Stop</th>
<th>Elapsed</th>
<th>Time Fuzziness</th>
</tr>
<?scm

(gtt-show-tasks (gtt-tasks (gtt-linked-project))
    (list   
        ''"<tr><td>"  gtt-task-memo ''"</td>\n"
        ''"<td colspan=4> </td>\n"
        ''</tr>
         (lambda (task) (gtt-ivls task
         (list

               ; the first column is blank
               ''"<tr><td> </td>\n"

               ; the second html table column shows the start date/time
               ''"<td>"  gtt-interval-start-str ''"</td>\n"
               
               ; the third html table column shows the stop date/time
               ''"<td>"  gtt-interval-stop-str ''"</td>\n"
               
               ; the fourth html table column shows the elapsed time
               ''"<td>"  gtt-interval-elapsed-str  ''"</td>\n"
               
               ; the fifth html table column shows the start/end time fuzziness
               ''"<td>"  gtt-interval-fuzz-str  ''"</td>\n"
               ''"</tr>"
         )))
    )
)


?>
</table>
                                         
<br><br>
That's all Folks!
</body>
</html>
